<TITLE> Italy senate head asked to form interim government </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ROME, Jan 30 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Italian President Giorgio Napolitano asked Senate President Franco Marini on Wednesday to try to form an interim government to reform voting rules ahead of new elections, a senior presidential aide said. Napolitano aide Donato Marra said the president had asked centre-left politician Marini, 74, to seek cross-party support for a temporary government after Prime Minister Romano Prodi's resignation last week.
